06/06/2006
TIRANA, Albania -- Danish Foreign Minister Per Stig Moeller kicked off a two-day official visit to Albania on Tuesday (6 June). 
In an interview with the daily Albanian News, he said even more reform efforts will be expected from the country after Albania's Stabilisation and Association Agreement with the EU is signed on 12 June, marking "the beginning of a new stage" in Albania-EU relations. 
He outlined several areas that require attention, including law and order -- specifically fighting organised crime and corruption. 
(Albanian News - 06/06/06)
